# NestJS Patterns

## Controllers — HTTP boundary only
Controllers translate HTTP in/out. Zero business logic.

```ts
// ✅ DO — delegate everything to the service
@Post()
@HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)
create(@Body() dto: CreateScenarioDto) {
  return this.scenariosService.create(dto);
}

// ❌ DON'T — logic in controller
@Post()
async create(@Body() dto: CreateScenarioDto) {
  if (!dto.name) return { error: 'missing name' };          // validation belongs in DTO
  const run = await this.prisma.scenarioRun.create(...);    // DB belongs in service
  return run;
}
```

## Services — own all logic and DB access
```ts
// ✅ DO
@Injectable()
export class ScenariosService {
  constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {}

  async findOne(id: string) {
    const run = await this.prisma.scenarioRun.findUnique({ where: { id } });
    if (!run) throw new NotFoundException(`ScenarioRun ${id} not found`);
    return run;
  }
}

// ❌ DON'T — instantiate dependencies manually
export class ScenariosService {
  private prisma = new PrismaClient();   // never — use DI
}
```

## Modules — one per feature
Every feature directory MUST have a `*.module.ts`.
`@Global()` is reserved for infrastructure: `PrismaModule`, `MetricsModule`.

```ts
// ✅ DO
@Module({
  controllers: [ScenariosController],
  providers: [ScenariosService],
})
export class ScenariosModule {}

// ❌ DON'T — register feature providers in AppModule directly
@Module({
  providers: [ScenariosService, AlertsService, ReportsService], // sprawl
})
export class AppModule {}
```

## DTOs — validate every incoming payload
```ts
// ✅ DO
export class CreateScenarioDto {
  @IsString()
  @IsNotEmpty()
  name: string;
}

// ❌ DON'T — untyped body
@Post()
create(@Body() body: any) { ... }
```

## Error handling — use NestJS exceptions
```ts
// ✅ DO
throw new NotFoundException(`ScenarioRun ${id} not found`);
throw new BadRequestException('name must not be empty');

// ❌ DON'T — raw errors leak stack traces to clients
throw new Error('not found');
return { error: 'something went wrong' };
```
